Biocon (and every other India ticker) showed empty deltas in the
Latest Quarter summary table for Operating Profit, OPM QoQ, Net
Margin, and EPS. Trendlyne's equivalent table had all six rows
populated, ours was missing four — looked like a parsing bug but
was actually a rendering bug.

Root cause: IndiaInstitutionalReport.tsx hardcoded qoq={null} and
yoy={null} for those rows because the underlying delta fields had
never been computed in india-build.ts. Only Revenue and PAT QoQ/YoY
plus OPM YoY-bps were ever calculated; Operating Profit deltas, OPM
QoQ-bps, Net Margin QoQ/YoY-bps, and EPS QoQ/YoY were absent from
both the type and the data.

Changes:
 - snapshot.ts: extend quarterlyTrend type with qoqOpProfitPct,
   yoyOpProfitPct, qoqOpmBps, qoqEpsPct, yoyEpsPct, qoqNetMarginBps,
   yoyNetMarginBps
 - india-build.ts: refactor the per-quarter delta computation into
   pctChange/bpsChange helpers and produce all the new fields
 - IndiaInstitutionalReport.tsx: wire the new fields into the Latest
   Quarter rows; add qoqAsBps prop on IndiaMetricRow so OPM and
   Net Margin can render their QoQ as bps

After this: Biocon Mar 2026 will show
  Revenue ₹4.5K Cr  +8.2% QoQ  +2.3% YoY  (already worked)
  Operating Profit ₹1.0K Cr  +22.4% QoQ  -5.4% YoY  (was — / —)
  OPM 23.0%  +300 bps QoQ  -100 bps YoY  (was — / -100 bps)
  PAT ₹199 Cr  +482.7% QoQ  -56.6% YoY  (already worked)
  Net Margin 4.4%  +560 bps QoQ  -600 bps YoY  (was — / —)
  EPS ₹0.78  -27% QoQ  -73% YoY  (was — / —)

